# Regression plan — check each update

When editing any of these regression-sensitive areas, follow this workflow so we do not reintroduce known issues.

## Before making changes

1. **Read** `docs/UPDATE_LOG_AND_REGRESSION_PLAN.md`:
   - **Section 4 (Regression checklist)** — run the checks that apply to the files you are touching.
   - **Section 7 (Do-not-break areas)** — ensure your change does not break the listed guarantees (worker token → environments, sidebar z-index, discovery logger, button styling, etc.).

2. If your change touches **sidebar/nav**, **worker token**, **discovery**, **flow buttons**, or **floating panels**: re-read the relevant Update log entries (Section 3) so you know what was fixed and why.

## After every fix

1. **Add an entry** to **Section 3 (Update log)** of `docs/UPDATE_LOG_AND_REGRESSION_PLAN.md`:
   - Short heading and one-line summary.
   - **Cause**, **Fix**, **Files**, **Regression check** (1–2 concrete steps).

2. If the fix is easy to regress, **add or update** a bullet in **Section 4 (Regression checklist)** for that area.

3. **Run** the relevant regression checks from Section 4 (and optionally **Section 5 — Quick regression checklist**) for the areas you changed.

## Do-not-break (quick reference)

| Area | Do not break |
|------|----------------|
| Sidebar / Navbar | z-index must stay ≥ 10050 so menu is never covered by floating log viewer (9999). |
| Worker token | Token source from modal; invalid `expiresAt` must not throw; `/environments` must load when token valid. |
| Discovery | Use `logger.info` only in discovery paths (no `logger.discovery` or `logger.success`). |
| Buttons (mock flows) | Buttons never grey when enabled; grey only when disabled. |
| Log viewer | Category filters must filter displayed content. |
| AppDiscoveryModalV8U | Backdrop is `div`, not `button`. |

This is the standard way for the IDE and agents to avoid reintroducing the errors documented in the regression plan.
